        <h3>Recent Additions Summary (Jan 2 - Daily Audit Update)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>✅ <strong>PLAN B.1 BUG FIX COMPLETE (2026-01-02 Chat 1):</strong> AI Message schema regression fixed - Production database missing metadata column that Result class defined. Applied ALTER TABLE ai_conversations ADD COLUMN metadata longtext NULL. 17 existing conversations lost message data during regression; historical data loss acknowledged; future operations should succeed</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>PLAN A.1 LOCKUP PREVENTION PROTOCOL (2026-01-02 Chat 2):</strong> Cleanup Agent lockup root cause analyzed: multi-file updates without /updateprompt checkpoints between files. FIX 1: Main Agent spec enforces /updateprompt as FIRST action + PATH A/B/C pattern. FIX 2: AGENT_REGISTRY.md v2.0→v2.2 consolidated. FIX 3: Cleanup Agent safety protocol requires record→edit→record per file</li>
            <li>🔴 <strong>CRITICAL FINDING: AGENT COMPLIANCE DEGRADATION (2026-01-02 Chat 2):</strong> Despite MANDATORY enforcement language, agent compliance regresses within 3-4 prompts. Agents read rules correctly but systematically violate them by prompt 5+. Root cause: Agent state/memory between prompts is optional, not persistent. Requires architectural change - not configuration cleanup. Evidence: Cleanup Agent Chat 2 Prompt 9 documented all violations. Recommendation: Escalate to agent architecture review</li>
            <li>✅ <strong>PLAN F.4 DOCUMENTATION SYNC (2026-01-02 Chat 3):</strong> DocumentationSync Agent updated 8 documentation files with Jan 2 audit findings. Files: ai_chat_system_audit.tt, AIChatConversationSavingFix.tt, AI_CHAT_DOCUMENTATION_FEATURE_SPEC.tt, database_configuration.tt, DAILY_WORKFLOW_TUTORIAL.tt, zencoder_reset_plan.tt, ZENCODER_AI_ASSISTANT_GUIDE.tt, AIIntegrationComprehensiveAudit.tt. All files versioned consistently (vX.YZ→vX.(YZ+1)), timestamped (Thu Jan 02 15:42-15:48 UTC), documented with Recent Changes sections</li>
            <li>📋 <strong>PLAN A.1 CONFIGURATION FIX FOLLOW-UP:</strong> Discovered and fixed 5 configuration files instructing automatic /sessionhandoff triggers (should be manual-only). Updated: daily-plan-automator-role.md, AGENT_REGISTRY.md, keywords-global.md, cleanup-agent-workflow.md, keywords.md. /sessionhandoff now correctly requires explicit user execution</li>
            <li>🎯 <strong>WEEK 1 EXECUTION ON TRACK:</strong> Jan 2 work completed: B.1 bug fix (AI Message schema), A.1 lockups prevented (3 fixes applied), critical agent compliance issue identified and escalated, documentation synchronized with audit findings. All Jan 2 priorities from Master Plan v0.15 addressed</li>
